      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:2:7",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/2/6",
      "text": [
        " «إِذَا جَرَى فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.6 - Ali ibn Ja'far asked his brother, Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as) about a roof where people urinate and perform ritual washing after major impurity (ghusl), and then it rains.\nHe asked: \"Can the water that flows from it be used for ablution (wudu) for prayer?\"\nImam (as) said: \"If it flows, there is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
